#X text 21 53 The "RANDOM-MIXER" module is a mixer that takes 4 inputs
with individual gain control and on/off toggles. It takes trigger/gate
signals to either randomly solo a channel or randomly mute channels.
With RANDOM-SOLO only one channel is active at the same time. With
RANDOM-MUTE any combinations of on and off states are possible. The
main purpose of the mixer is to in a musical but unpredictable way
switch between different kinds of material. It also features 4 effects:
reverb \, delay \, overdrive and bitcrush. Set the effect level with
the purple FXSEND slider and choose effect with the button underneath
the slider. Send a trigger/gate signal to the FX input to randomly
change type of effect. The module can be used as a simple tool to manually
turn material on or off or become a creative sequencer by for example
sending various percussive sounds to channels 1-4 and using various
trigger sources to the FX \, SOLO & MUTE inputs.;
#X text 25 344 GREEN TOGGLES - turn channels on or off;
#X text 25 368 FX BUTTON (right of green toggles) - press to change
FX;
#X text 25 392 FXSEND - set the amount of FX;
#X text 25 416 RANDOM-SOLO - click to randomly select a channel to
be solo;
#X text 25 440 RANDOM-MUTE - click to randomly mute any channel;
